    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I tend to think it's not fixable with the current approach. The html anchors are buggy in qt TextEdit and I couldn't find any workaround. I've been looking for a workaround to replace the html anchors with other tags and add styling to the text, but the qt rich text processor is formatting the text in unexpected ways and the input tags are altered in such a way that the hyperlink cannot be properly identified.\r\n\r\nE.g. One approach I've tried was to add styling to the hyperlink text using `style` and mark the hyperlink with anchors. It was promising, but the hyperlink is split after the first letter by the rich text processor `<span..>h</span><span ...>ttp://www.etc.ro</span>`\r\n\r\nWhat we need in order to fix this is to find a way to style the urls and check all these requirements:\r\n1. Add styling to substrings (this is easy and fully supported with `style`)\r\n2. Identify each url that has been styled (there are changes that needs to be applied so that we can remove the styling. Sometimes a substring will remain when the url is invalidated and the styling needs to be removed). Something like html `class`, `id`, or any other way to preserve some unique metadata in the html tag. @caybro @micieslak @noeliaSD @alexandraB99 Any ideas on this? The ones already mentioned are not working.\r\n3. Identify identical urls so that we can highlight them (add background color)\r\n4. Move all white spaces outside of the url styling tag\r\n",
