    "body": "> @benjthayer One workaround I can think of is to select the hyperlink on click (the same way we're doing for mentions). WDYT of this workaround?\r\n\r\nThanks @alexjba , I think the priority here is to retain optimal usability for the editing of the URL. The user doesn't need to be able to click and visit the link from the composer given they have already copied it so it is in their clipboard or browser if they want to use/view the link. So even when the link is in the blue treatment indicating that the string is a URL, we can retain the type (I-beam cursor) when the user hovers the string as opposed to the pointer cursor. Much like Discord does... \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/110033914/746cb39c-fce8-41ef-b62e-a3a9644acf06\r\n\r\nEssentially, whether the user uses their mouse or arrow keys to move the I-beam cursor into the string, any subsequent editing shouldn't delete the entire URL unless the user has first highlighted the entire URL and hit the delete key.\r\n\r\nOne thing to note is that we should also retain the double-click and triple-click functionality that we have in the app today.  eg if I double-click `currencies` or `status` in the following string, just that section should be highlighted so I can edit that segment: https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/status/. \r\n(Triple-click should highlight the entire row of type in the composer)\r\n\r\n",
